def: The beginning of the day, or first appearance of light; thedawn; hence, the beginning. Milton.The tender mercy of our God; whereby the dayspring from on high hathvisited us. Luke i. 78.
Of or pertaining to micrococci; caused by micrococci. Nature.
Of or pertaining to Pelusium, an ancient city of Egypt; as, thePelusiac (or former eastern) outlet of the Nile.
The state of being an ordinary. [R.] Fuller.
A plant producing an umbel or umbels.
The act of seizing or taking hold of Catching bargain (Law), abargain made with an heir expectant for the purchase of hisexpectancy at an inadequate price. Bouvier.
